WEBVTT

00:07.442 --> 00:08.530
Previously on "All Rise"...

00:08.573 --> 00:09.922
Got a very expensive
defense attorney

00:09.966 --> 00:11.402
waiting for me
in my office.

00:11.446 --> 00:13.056
- Amy Quinn.
- How'd you know?

00:13.100 --> 00:14.666
That smile. You always
had a thing for Quinn.

00:14.710 --> 00:16.625
- Not true.
- Okay, not true.

00:16.668 --> 00:18.583
If we found out you had
something to do with this, Amy,

00:18.627 --> 00:20.411
you won't just be disbarred.
You'll go to jail.

00:20.455 --> 00:21.804
Well, that's a big gun.
I thought we liked each other.

00:21.847 --> 00:23.719
Emily Lopez-Batista.

00:23.762 --> 00:25.590
Not all double-barrel names
work, but yours does.

00:25.634 --> 00:27.375
For the record,
my name is Emily Lopez.

00:27.418 --> 00:29.203
- Where'd the Batista go?
- He's living with his mother.

00:29.246 --> 00:31.074
- I like you.
- I like you.

00:31.118 --> 00:33.555
There's gonna be a divorce.
I don't know how much time I--

00:33.598 --> 00:36.036
Em, whatever works for you
works for me, okay?

00:36.079 --> 00:37.037
Em.

00:40.083 --> 00:47.786
♪♪♪

00:47.830 --> 00:49.788
Woman: Put your bag
on the belt, sir.

00:49.832 --> 00:51.573
Symbol of a doomed marriage.

00:51.616 --> 00:52.922
Is that
your engagement ring?

00:52.965 --> 00:55.533
- He wants it back.
- And you couldn't resist.

00:55.577 --> 00:56.578
Can we talk
about something else?

00:56.621 --> 00:58.058
You had to try it on
one last time.

00:58.101 --> 00:59.842
Like how I have to
cross-examine a priest today?

00:59.885 --> 01:02.236
First time for everything.My question is
why you left it on.

01:02.279 --> 01:03.846
I know it's not a sin
to cross-examine a priest,

01:03.889 --> 01:05.674
but does the judge?
Does God?

01:05.717 --> 01:08.329
Tell me it's not because
you've changed your mind.

01:08.372 --> 01:12.289
[ indistinct conversations ]

01:12.333 --> 01:14.422
[ laughter ]

01:14.465 --> 01:18.904
[ indistinct conversations
continue ]

01:18.948 --> 01:21.255
It is like
a literal sea of love.

01:21.298 --> 01:22.952
I like Wedding Day.

01:22.995 --> 01:25.911
They don't know what
they're getting into.

01:25.955 --> 01:28.566
[ indistinct conversations ]

01:28.610 --> 01:30.525
- Are you nervous?
- No!

01:30.568 --> 01:32.135
Mark:
Benner does this PR thing.

01:32.179 --> 01:35.007
Civilians running around,
taking all the parking spaces,

01:35.051 --> 01:37.140
throwing bouquets,
flowers everywhere.

01:37.184 --> 01:38.750
- Like bridal bouquets?
- Yeah.

01:38.794 --> 01:40.143
You should see what they try
and sneak through security with.

01:40.187 --> 01:41.797
- You never told me.
- Once a year.

01:41.840 --> 01:44.756
We weren't together
a year ago.Sounds fun. Is it fun?

01:44.800 --> 01:47.803
- If you like getting married.
- [ chuckles ]

01:47.846 --> 01:50.110
So my last meeting with
the skin care company is at 3.

01:50.153 --> 01:51.633
What time do you think
you'll be done?

01:51.676 --> 01:53.156
Mm, early, I hope.

01:53.200 --> 01:55.071
Depends on how this
preliminary hearing goes.

01:55.115 --> 01:56.333
Well,
by the end of the day,

01:56.377 --> 01:58.118
I should officially be
a brand ambassador.

01:58.161 --> 01:59.945
- Hey.
- We can celebrate.

01:59.989 --> 02:01.686
Sounds good. Go out to dinner,
grab some bubbles.

02:01.730 --> 02:03.993
- I'd like to get married.
- Now?

02:04.036 --> 02:06.430
No. But...sometime.

02:06.474 --> 02:08.084
Can we not do this today?

02:08.128 --> 02:10.042
I'm not...doing anything.

02:10.086 --> 02:12.393
Can I kiss you now?
'Cause I need to get to court.

02:12.436 --> 02:14.134
Oh.

02:14.177 --> 02:16.223
You know I really dig you,
right?

02:16.266 --> 02:19.051
I...really dig you.

02:19.095 --> 02:21.184
Oh.

02:21.228 --> 02:22.620
[ keys jangle ]

02:22.664 --> 02:23.882
Drive safe.

02:23.926 --> 02:25.710
[ closes door ]

02:25.754 --> 02:27.756
[ elevator bell dings ]

02:27.799 --> 02:29.540
Oh, babe,
I love you so much.

02:29.584 --> 02:31.412
[ gasps ]
You look amazing!

02:31.455 --> 02:34.241
Well, we should.
It's our wedding day.

02:34.284 --> 02:36.634
We're excited!Sara, I have to meet
with my client.

02:36.678 --> 02:38.158
All right. Congratulations.

02:38.201 --> 02:39.159
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

02:39.202 --> 02:40.334
Also, I haven't
changed my mind.

02:40.377 --> 02:41.900
Then why
are you still--

02:41.944 --> 02:44.033
He proposed. I accepted.
It's mine. That's the deal.

02:44.076 --> 02:45.991
Emily,
you're getting a divorce.

02:46.035 --> 02:48.385
He says
it's a family heirloom.Then you should give it back.

02:48.429 --> 02:51.693
Except he lies...a lot.
Also, I can't. It's stuck.

02:51.736 --> 02:53.825
[ sighs ]

02:53.869 --> 02:56.567
In this matter, the imposition
of sentence is suspended,

02:56.611 --> 02:59.222
and you are placed
on 36 months' formal probation

02:59.266 --> 03:01.616
under the following
terms and conditions--

03:01.659 --> 03:03.879
pay a fine of $500.
- Your Honor, that ain't right.

03:03.922 --> 03:05.837
Mr. Owens,
you've done a decent job

03:05.881 --> 03:08.013
of representing yourself.
Don't ruin it.

03:08.057 --> 03:10.842
Selling marijuana is illegal
without a license.

03:10.886 --> 03:13.018
Impossible for a man like me
to get a license

03:13.062 --> 03:14.542
when most go
to big white corporations.

03:14.585 --> 03:17.849
Mr. Owens--They got me when I was
coming up as a kid.

03:17.893 --> 03:19.373
And now that I'm going
down the other side,

03:19.416 --> 03:21.288
they got me again.

03:21.331 --> 03:23.420
Impossible for a man like...

03:25.509 --> 03:27.990
It's impossible
for a man like me

03:28.033 --> 03:30.166
to have a chance.

03:30.210 --> 03:32.037
The court will allow
extra time

03:32.081 --> 03:33.691
for payment of fines
and court costs.

03:33.735 --> 03:36.259
Court costs, too?
With respect,

03:36.303 --> 03:38.218
why does Your Honor think
a man like me

03:38.261 --> 03:40.611
was selling weed
in the first place?

03:41.917 --> 03:43.962
Am I dismissed, Your Honor?

03:49.098 --> 03:50.230
Attorney: Your Honor.

03:54.190 --> 03:55.670
The man has a point.

03:57.237 --> 03:59.151
What are the court costs
anyway?

03:59.195 --> 04:01.502
- Your Honor?
- Court costs on this case.

04:01.545 --> 04:04.287
They change all the time.
The clerk's office--

04:04.331 --> 04:06.202
Gonna wander over there
and stretch my legs a bit.

04:06.246 --> 04:08.726
- Your Honor has a bench trial.
- In 30 minutes.

04:08.770 --> 04:10.206
I can call down to the clerk
and have them send--

04:10.250 --> 04:11.990
I'm feeling
a little hemmed in.

04:12.034 --> 04:14.166
I want to get my steps in
and take in

04:14.210 --> 04:16.473
the Wedding Day sights.
- A judge out there is like

04:16.517 --> 04:19.694
a butterfly landing
on your hand.

04:19.737 --> 04:21.913
Judges are strongly
discouraged

04:21.957 --> 04:23.698
from using public areas
of the courthouse.

04:23.741 --> 04:25.613
Not a law,
not even a rule.

04:25.656 --> 04:27.484
No. Accepted wisdom.

04:27.528 --> 04:29.617
Deputy Watkins,
does it seem right to you

04:29.660 --> 04:31.532
that judges are imprisoned
in their chambers,

04:31.575 --> 04:33.273
cut off
from the general public

04:33.316 --> 04:36.450
and the carrot cake muffins
in the cafeteria?

04:39.627 --> 04:41.542
I can run and get that muffin
for you, if you like.

04:41.585 --> 04:44.936
You're more afraid of her
than me?

04:47.156 --> 04:48.592
Fine.

04:50.202 --> 04:52.074
Maybe I'll go later.

04:52.117 --> 04:53.728
Lola Carmichael is one

04:53.771 --> 04:55.120
of the fairest judges
in the building.

04:55.164 --> 04:57.775
- Is she Catholic?
- I-I don't have any idea.

04:57.819 --> 05:00.343
- If she is, I'm dead.
- The prosecution's case

05:00.387 --> 05:02.432
is almost
entirely circumstantial.Yeah, but if the Church

05:02.476 --> 05:04.260
wants to blame someone,
it usually works.

05:04.304 --> 05:06.436
Felony grand theft?
100 grand?

05:06.480 --> 05:08.525
Our goal is just to raise
reasonable doubt.

05:08.569 --> 05:10.310
Well, it isn't possible

05:10.353 --> 05:12.094
for one person
to skim that much.

05:14.792 --> 05:17.055
But you don't believe me

05:17.099 --> 05:19.188
because I was--
because I lived on Skid Row,

05:19.231 --> 05:21.451
because I've stolen before,
because of the hair?

05:21.495 --> 05:22.887
I had a shaved head
in high school.

05:22.931 --> 05:24.976
Your hair doesn't bother me.
And what I don't believe

05:25.020 --> 05:26.151
is that you've told me
everything I need to know

05:26.195 --> 05:28.676
to properly defend you.

05:28.719 --> 05:30.678
It's not too late. Give me
a list of your friends.

05:30.721 --> 05:32.723
I can find at least one
character witness.

05:32.767 --> 05:34.246
I either ripped them off
or owe them money.

05:34.290 --> 05:35.509
- Family, then.
- Told you I don't have any,

05:35.552 --> 05:38.381
not since I ran away.
Just the sister.

05:38.425 --> 05:40.252
The same sister who's
testifying against you?

05:40.296 --> 05:42.733
[ cellphone chimes ]

05:42.777 --> 05:44.692
We need to get in there.

05:44.735 --> 05:52.352
♪♪♪

05:52.395 --> 05:55.616
Emily: The prosecution has asked
that the court not be fooled.

05:55.659 --> 05:56.878
They are saying, in fact,

05:56.921 --> 05:58.575
that my client's
religious garments

05:58.619 --> 06:00.272
are nothing more than a ruse

06:00.316 --> 06:02.405
and that Sister Phoebe
must have $100,000

06:02.449 --> 06:03.928
hidden under her habit somewhere

06:03.972 --> 06:05.582
because, as I will
demonstrate, Your Honor,

06:05.626 --> 06:08.193
they haven't bothered
to look anywhere else.No!

06:08.237 --> 06:10.282
My wife, who's not yet--

06:10.326 --> 06:11.806
I really need
to make her my wife,

06:11.849 --> 06:13.677
but right now she's in labor
big-time.

06:13.721 --> 06:15.853
- I'll call the paramedics.
- Judge Benner isn't here yet.

06:15.897 --> 06:17.289
Your Honor, can you...

06:17.333 --> 06:18.813
We need to be married
before the baby's born.

06:18.856 --> 06:21.293
[ gallery murmuring ]

06:21.337 --> 06:25.733
♪♪♪

06:25.776 --> 06:28.257
[ woman panting ] Ohh.
And my water broke.

06:28.300 --> 06:30.041
This kid wants out,
but not before I get that ring.

06:30.085 --> 06:32.479
Ooh. Let's get you
comfortable.

06:32.522 --> 06:34.089
Let's give them some room,
people.

06:34.132 --> 06:35.177
- What are your names?
- I'm Ryan.

06:35.220 --> 06:37.309
- Corina.
- Judge Carmichael. Lola.

06:37.353 --> 06:39.921
Is that a nun?
I can't get married by a nun.

06:39.964 --> 06:41.705
My grandmother's Orthodox.
She'll kill me!

06:41.749 --> 06:46.362
May I offer my services
at Atheist Reverend CXR301?

06:46.406 --> 06:49.104
No!It absolutely has to be
a nondenominational ceremony.

06:49.147 --> 06:50.584
- Judge Carmichael?
- I got you.

06:50.627 --> 06:52.020
Have you done this before,
Your Honor?

06:52.063 --> 06:54.414
No, but I'm feeling inspired.
Where are the rings?

06:54.457 --> 06:57.242
[ panting ]

06:57.286 --> 06:59.375
- Give me your hands.
- [ panting ]

06:59.419 --> 07:02.160
We form this circle
to celebrate the people

07:02.204 --> 07:04.075
who have created
this little miracle

07:04.119 --> 07:05.250
about to enter this world.

07:05.294 --> 07:06.730
[ laughs ]

07:06.774 --> 07:09.385
It's the day that you promise
to yourselves

07:09.429 --> 07:12.301
and to this little child
to live in love.

07:12.344 --> 07:13.737
No matter what happens
between the two of you,

07:13.781 --> 07:16.348
you will always share
something.

07:16.392 --> 07:19.613
May you forever take comfort
in this romance!Ohh!

07:19.656 --> 07:21.092
Thank you,
Judge Carmichael.

07:21.136 --> 07:23.399
Not done yet.
Do you and you?

07:23.443 --> 07:24.574
- I do.
- I do.

07:24.618 --> 07:26.271
You are now husband and wife.

07:26.315 --> 07:28.796
Oh. Wait.
It's tradition.

07:28.839 --> 07:32.713
[ panting ]

07:34.497 --> 07:37.892
[ moaning loudly ]Seriously,
get to the hospital.

07:37.935 --> 07:40.242
[ panting ]

07:40.285 --> 07:42.287
♪♪♪

07:50.557 --> 07:52.167
[ indistinct conversations ]

07:52.210 --> 07:54.082
Callan.
I scooped this case

07:54.125 --> 07:55.475
when I saw you were
the prosecutor.

07:55.518 --> 07:56.780
Amy Quinn.
Nice to see you.

07:56.824 --> 07:58.173
Thought it might be
a fun rematch.

07:58.216 --> 08:01.306
Hmm.This is Mark Callan,
our nemesis.

08:01.350 --> 08:03.483
- I'm Margo.
- I know.

08:03.526 --> 08:04.919
Your client's guilty.

08:04.962 --> 08:06.790
Way to get
ahead of yourself.

08:06.834 --> 08:08.226
This isn't even a trial.

08:08.270 --> 08:10.054
She's a serial
dine and dasher.

08:10.098 --> 08:11.926
She stuck 12 men
with huge bills.

08:11.969 --> 08:13.231
They're sitting right there.

08:13.275 --> 08:14.798
It's called dating,
not felony extortion.

08:14.842 --> 08:18.541
And 12 is a little overkill
for a preliminary hearing.

08:18.585 --> 08:21.370
I'll make you a bet.
It's just a prelim.

08:21.413 --> 08:23.415
If Judge Laski
throws extortion out

08:23.459 --> 08:25.069
or bounces it,
you buy dinner.

08:25.113 --> 08:26.462
If he allows us
to go to trial,

08:26.506 --> 08:27.898
I buy dinner.

08:27.942 --> 08:29.639
I don't gamble with the lives
of defendants, Amy.

08:29.683 --> 08:31.641
Oh, I don't mind.
I like a bit of fun.

08:31.685 --> 08:33.687
- Thanks, but no.
- Okay.

08:33.730 --> 08:36.037
I don't need any incentive
to kick your ass.

08:36.080 --> 08:37.778
[ elevator bell dings ]I'll do it for free.

08:37.821 --> 08:40.563
See you in there, counselor.

08:40.607 --> 08:42.609
[ sighs ] Gentlemen.

08:42.652 --> 08:45.133
Just got the word.

08:45.176 --> 08:47.875
[ door closes ]We will be back any minute now.

08:47.918 --> 08:50.617
Happy to resume battle
with Ms. Lopez-Batista.

08:50.660 --> 08:52.619
Lopez. It's just Lopez.

08:56.057 --> 08:57.667
It--It's not staying.

08:57.711 --> 08:59.974
- Sorry. What?
- The ring.

09:00.017 --> 09:02.237
- [ softly ] Just forget it.
- [ whispers ] Okay.

09:04.587 --> 09:05.936
[ clears throat ]

09:05.980 --> 09:08.330
I have to wait for mine.
I'm a novice.

09:08.373 --> 09:09.853
I don't become
a bride of Christ

09:09.897 --> 09:11.942
till my commitment
ceremony.

09:11.986 --> 09:13.683
Then I get a ring.

09:13.727 --> 09:17.992
Unless I go to jail.
Then I get excommunicated,

09:18.035 --> 09:19.602
which means it's your job
to make sure

09:19.646 --> 09:21.038
I don't leave our Lord
at the altar.

09:21.082 --> 09:22.779
I will do everything
I can.

09:24.041 --> 09:25.565
Luke: All rise.

09:27.218 --> 09:29.003
Then about a year ago,
we put Sister Phoebe

09:29.046 --> 09:30.787
in charge of
the Sunday cash donations.

09:30.831 --> 09:32.093
So she had access to the money.

09:32.136 --> 09:33.703
That's right.
We had to do an audit.

09:33.747 --> 09:35.009
[ exhales deeply ]
I hate math.

09:35.052 --> 09:36.576
Baptisms are easier.

09:36.619 --> 09:39.753
It showed revenues were
below historical averages.

09:39.796 --> 09:41.406
The pattern started shortly

09:41.450 --> 09:43.365
after Sister Phoebe was
given those responsibilities.

09:43.408 --> 09:45.846
Thank you, sir--Father.

09:45.889 --> 09:47.717
Ms. Lopez?

09:50.807 --> 09:53.331
Father Vincent, when you met
my client, what did you think?

09:53.375 --> 09:55.638
I mean, the hair,
her checkered past.

09:55.682 --> 09:58.075
We don't usually pick
our future nuns off the street,

09:58.119 --> 09:59.381
but she was honest

09:59.424 --> 10:01.209
about her complications
with the law.

10:01.252 --> 10:03.167
And she settled,
found her vocation.

10:03.211 --> 10:05.343
Not shy, that one.
She challenged my homily

10:05.387 --> 10:07.041
on the homeless
and addiction.

10:07.084 --> 10:08.782
She was right.

10:08.825 --> 10:11.698
You like Phoebe.
You trusted her.

10:11.741 --> 10:13.656
I did,
before she stole from us.

10:13.700 --> 10:15.092
- Move to strike.
- Sustained.

10:15.136 --> 10:17.399
Did you find any evidence
when you searched her room?

10:17.442 --> 10:18.922
Cash, expensive purchases?

10:18.966 --> 10:20.532
- No.
- And yet you assume

10:20.576 --> 10:22.056
this young woman
would risk her vocation

10:22.099 --> 10:24.058
and life that she is
so fiercely committed to.

10:24.101 --> 10:25.363
Objection. Speculation.

10:25.407 --> 10:27.670
Withdrawn.

10:27.714 --> 10:30.194
The donations--Who handles
the cash between

10:30.238 --> 10:32.196
the parishioners and the bank?
Could you provide names?

10:32.240 --> 10:34.198
Well, there are a few--
ushers, volunteers,

10:34.242 --> 10:35.983
our accountant.
I can get you the list.

10:36.026 --> 10:38.638
So Phoebe isn't the only person
who had access to the money.

10:38.681 --> 10:41.031
No.Just the only one
you picked up off the street.

10:41.075 --> 10:43.773
♪♪♪

10:43.817 --> 10:45.732
She winked at me.

10:45.775 --> 10:47.603
So that's how the defendant
first made contact.

10:47.647 --> 10:49.823
Yeah. She--She winked at me
on the dating site,

10:49.866 --> 10:51.389
then we messaged a bit,

10:51.433 --> 10:53.087
then, uh, then she asked me
out to dinner.

10:53.130 --> 10:56.003
- And how'd that make you feel?
- I'd kind of given up on being,

10:56.046 --> 10:57.874
I don't know, whatever,

10:57.918 --> 11:00.572
attractive to anybody
ever,

11:00.616 --> 11:04.054
so yeah, it felt good.
She liked me.

11:04.098 --> 11:05.447
Tell us about your dinner.

11:05.490 --> 11:07.710
Margo told me to order
anything I liked.

11:07.754 --> 11:10.452
She ordered the wine,
a 2010 Burgundy.

11:10.495 --> 11:12.933
I remember 'cause I kept
staring at the bill after,

11:12.976 --> 11:17.024
thinking, who pays this much
for a bottle of freakin' wine?

11:17.067 --> 11:21.898
I guess I did. $918.35.

11:21.942 --> 11:24.509
I am so sorry
that happened to you, Colin.

11:24.553 --> 11:26.120
No further questions.

11:26.163 --> 11:28.209
Ms. Quinn, care to cross?

11:28.252 --> 11:30.951
I'd love to, Your Honor.

11:30.994 --> 11:32.735
Ahem. So you messaged
with Margo.

11:32.779 --> 11:34.737
Is that because you thought
she was attractive?

11:34.781 --> 11:36.783
Yes. Yeah.

11:36.826 --> 11:38.959
And you said
that you'd given up on love.

11:39.002 --> 11:41.744
That's horrible. No one should
have to feel that way.

11:41.788 --> 11:45.400
- I haven't been out since.
- I understand.

11:45.443 --> 11:48.098
Colin, before
your date with Margo,

11:48.142 --> 11:49.839
how long had it been
since you had sex?

11:49.883 --> 11:52.015
I mean, with another person.

11:52.059 --> 11:53.538
- Objection.
- Overruled.

11:53.582 --> 11:55.279
Colin,
did you use the phrase

11:55.323 --> 11:56.585
"sticking it to the soufflé"
that night

11:56.628 --> 11:58.761
when talking to my client?

11:58.805 --> 12:00.197
Did you say that's
what you were gonna do

12:00.241 --> 12:02.765
to her after dinner?
That you would stick it to her?

12:02.809 --> 12:04.158
- Objection!
- Sit down, Callan.

12:04.201 --> 12:05.986
I'm looking forward
to the answer to that question.

12:06.029 --> 12:07.988
It was just--I didn't--
I didn't mean it

12:08.031 --> 12:09.685
to be disgusting
like you just said!

12:09.729 --> 12:11.426
- I was trying--
- No wonder she left early.

12:11.469 --> 12:12.949
Verbally assaulted like this?

12:12.993 --> 12:14.908
I mean, who knows
what would have happened

12:14.951 --> 12:17.040
if she had stuck around
for dessert?

12:17.084 --> 12:19.260
No more questions, Your Honor.

12:20.565 --> 12:23.438
Step down, Mr. O'Mara.

12:23.481 --> 12:25.962
Well, all this talk
about food and drink

12:26.006 --> 12:28.051
has got my stomach all grumbly.

12:28.095 --> 12:30.184
Lunch recess. Back at 1:30.

12:30.227 --> 12:31.533
[ gavel bangs ]

12:31.576 --> 12:36.190
[ gallery murmuring ]

12:36.233 --> 12:38.975
[ indistinct conversations
in distance ]

12:43.066 --> 12:45.895
You should come over
tonight.

12:45.939 --> 12:48.202
I've got tools that'll snap
that sucker right off.

12:48.245 --> 12:51.335
I used to have a rosary.

12:51.379 --> 12:53.424
I still have mine
from when I was baptized.

12:53.468 --> 12:56.253
Reminds me of my abuelita.

12:56.297 --> 12:59.387
[ footsteps approach ]

12:59.430 --> 13:00.997
- Sister.
- Sara: That your next victim?

13:01.041 --> 13:04.435
Sister Miranda.
Parish accountant.

13:04.479 --> 13:06.568
Taking apart
a priest anda nun--

13:06.611 --> 13:08.483
you better find
that rosary.

13:08.526 --> 13:12.400
She doesn't look well.

13:12.443 --> 13:14.228
See you back in there.

13:17.013 --> 13:20.060
Woman in distance:
Congratulations.

13:23.324 --> 13:26.066
Sister Miranda, you testified
as the parish accountant

13:26.109 --> 13:29.243
that Phoebe had direct access
to the collection monies.

13:29.286 --> 13:32.681
Did you ever actually see her
take any cash?I did not.

13:32.724 --> 13:34.291
Do the sisters at your church
have your own income?

13:34.335 --> 13:35.815
A small allowance.

13:35.858 --> 13:38.208
I save up mine
for action movies.

13:38.252 --> 13:40.994
Isn't it true that
Phoebe gives hers away?Objection. Relevance.

13:41.037 --> 13:43.431
My client has been accused
of taking money.

13:43.474 --> 13:45.085
I think it's relevant if she's
known to be giving it away.

13:45.128 --> 13:47.174
Overruled. You may answer.

13:47.217 --> 13:49.393
When we met, she was
living on the street

13:49.437 --> 13:52.440
and so angry
but also so kind.

13:52.483 --> 13:55.095
If somebody needed it
and Phoebe had it,

13:55.138 --> 13:58.272
she was always giving
more than she has.

13:58.315 --> 14:00.274
Under direct examination,
you said that you never heard

14:00.317 --> 14:03.146
my client complaining
about not having money.

14:03.190 --> 14:04.931
One of our vows is poverty.

14:04.974 --> 14:08.499
She went from a tent to
an abbey. She was grateful.

14:08.543 --> 14:10.937
You also testified that you saw
her argue with Father Vincent

14:10.980 --> 14:13.591
about how the church's money
was being allocated.

14:13.635 --> 14:16.856
Father Vincent planned
to renovate the rectory.

14:16.899 --> 14:20.250
She wanted all our resources
to go where it mattered--

14:20.294 --> 14:23.079
Skid Row.
- You've dedicated yourself

14:23.123 --> 14:25.647
to a life of service
to the poor.

14:25.690 --> 14:28.215
What do you think
of the rectory?Objection. Relevance.

14:28.258 --> 14:30.521
- Ms. Lopez.
- The DDA is suggesting

14:30.565 --> 14:32.784
that a nun had motive
to steal money

14:32.828 --> 14:34.308
that was intended
to fix the rectory.

14:34.351 --> 14:36.397
Your Honor.Maybe others share
the same motive.

14:36.440 --> 14:37.964
Like a group nun heist?
Your Honor--

14:38.007 --> 14:40.575
It goes
to reasonable doubt.

14:40.618 --> 14:42.794
That's the relevance,
Your Honor.

14:42.838 --> 14:43.926
Overruled.

14:43.970 --> 14:45.885
Sister Miranda,

14:45.928 --> 14:48.322
knowing my client
as you do,

14:48.365 --> 14:52.152
out of all the ushers
and volunteers,

14:52.195 --> 14:54.154
isn't it possible that one--
- No.

14:56.547 --> 14:57.461
Uh...

15:07.863 --> 15:11.736
Phoebe says it wasn't her.
You say it wasn't them.

15:11.780 --> 15:13.608
According to Father Vincent,

15:13.651 --> 15:16.959
the only other person who had
access is the accountant.

15:17.003 --> 15:19.135
Sister Miranda, aren't you
the church accountant?

15:19.179 --> 15:22.617
Objection. Sister Miranda
isn't the nun on trial here.

15:22.660 --> 15:24.140
It's a simple question,
Your Honor.

15:26.186 --> 15:27.143
I...

15:28.753 --> 15:30.581
- Maybe it's time--
- Hold that thought.

15:30.625 --> 15:31.539
Counsel, approach the bench.

15:37.632 --> 15:38.807
[ lowered voice ]
My obligation

15:38.850 --> 15:40.809
is to the fairness
of this process,

15:40.852 --> 15:42.332
not the outcome,
but it appears

15:42.376 --> 15:44.900
your witness was about
to either incriminate herself

15:44.944 --> 15:46.423
or commit perjury.

15:46.467 --> 15:47.903
Fifth Amendment,
Mr. Berger.

15:47.947 --> 15:50.079
I appreciate
Your Honor's wisdom.

15:50.123 --> 15:52.125
- Move to dismiss, Your Honor.
- The charges stand.

15:52.168 --> 15:53.996
I said "either."

15:54.040 --> 15:55.998
You two figure out
which one it is,

15:56.042 --> 15:58.348
and we'll come back
after our lunch recess.

15:58.392 --> 15:59.654
[ gavel bangs ]

15:59.697 --> 16:04.964
♪♪♪

16:14.190 --> 16:15.844
Who knew
nuns could be so dramatic?

16:15.887 --> 16:17.889
I did.

16:17.933 --> 16:19.152
Where's Judge Benner?

16:19.195 --> 16:21.154
There's a long line
of the great unwed

16:21.197 --> 16:22.851
outside her courtroom
waiting to get hitched.

16:22.894 --> 16:25.288
- Apparently, she's late.
- Better not be much longer.

16:25.332 --> 16:28.378
The brides are getting
restless.It's not like her.

16:28.422 --> 16:30.728
Wedding Day's a special day
for Judge Benner.

16:30.772 --> 16:31.991
I always thought the whole
thing was a bit weird.

16:32.034 --> 16:34.732
Well, nice but weird.

16:34.776 --> 16:36.691
I like it very much.
Every other day of the year,

16:36.734 --> 16:38.562
the people
who come to this building

16:38.606 --> 16:40.738
are having one of the worst
days of their lives.

16:40.782 --> 16:43.350
Today we get to be part
of one of the best.

16:45.482 --> 16:49.486
I always knew it.
You're actually all soft inside.

16:49.530 --> 16:51.401
Your Honor--

16:55.101 --> 16:58.060
Y--Your Honor.

17:01.455 --> 17:04.284
Oh.

17:05.328 --> 17:07.069
Going to the clerk's office.
You haven't see me.

17:07.113 --> 17:08.897
[ squeals ]

17:08.940 --> 17:10.899
[ door opens ]

17:10.942 --> 17:12.248
Your Honor!

17:18.254 --> 17:21.040
- Where is she?
- I haven't seen her.

17:22.563 --> 17:23.868
Why didn't you let me
submit Miranda

17:23.912 --> 17:25.609
as a character witness?

17:25.653 --> 17:28.134
Because Father Vincent told her
to testify for the prosecution.

17:28.177 --> 17:30.005
Or is it because you didn't
want me to figure out

17:30.049 --> 17:32.442
that she was the one
who actually stole the money?Is that our judge?

17:32.486 --> 17:35.576
I--No, I don't-- Maybe. They
don't usually let them out here.

17:35.619 --> 17:37.230
I think it was her.

17:37.273 --> 17:39.014
Phoebe, why are you taking
the fall for Miranda?

17:39.058 --> 17:41.799
I'm not. I'm standing trial
for a crime I didn't commit.

17:45.977 --> 17:48.371
You don't want to know

17:48.415 --> 17:50.634
what I was doing
on the street.

17:50.678 --> 17:53.246
Sister Miranda...

17:53.289 --> 17:55.378
Sister Miranda brought me
into the church.

17:55.422 --> 17:57.989
Early on, she could have busted
me on a parole violation.

17:58.033 --> 18:00.818
Literally caught me
with my hand in her purse.

18:00.862 --> 18:02.777
But she forgave me.

18:02.820 --> 18:05.127
She saved me.

18:05.171 --> 18:07.347
- That's no reason to--
- She's sick.

18:09.262 --> 18:12.308
Sister Miranda won't last
six months in jail.

18:12.352 --> 18:13.875
♪♪♪

18:13.918 --> 18:15.920
Mark: Off the record,
what is up with your client?

18:15.964 --> 18:17.966
Margo Baxter
is like Katharine Hepburn

18:18.009 --> 18:19.533
stuck in an episode
of "Happy Days."

18:19.576 --> 18:21.056
The Beckett play?

18:21.100 --> 18:23.711
No. The '70s sitcom
set in the '50s.

18:23.754 --> 18:25.104
How old areyou?

18:25.147 --> 18:27.106
My dad used to watch
the reruns.

18:27.149 --> 18:28.933
- Let's make a deal!
- You first.

18:28.977 --> 18:31.153
Three years' probation,

18:31.197 --> 18:33.068
30 days Caltrans
freeway cleanup.

18:33.112 --> 18:35.026
- Oh, that's sweet.
- That's the best I can--

18:35.070 --> 18:36.550
Wait. Sweet?

18:36.593 --> 18:38.900
I can picture you
sitting on your daddy's lap

18:38.943 --> 18:40.423
watching TV, eating chips.

18:40.467 --> 18:41.816
- Yeah.
- It's sweet.

18:41.859 --> 18:43.165
- No, that never happened.
- No deal.

18:43.209 --> 18:44.949
Drop the charges.
[ crunching ]

18:44.993 --> 18:46.647
Your client systematically
lured these men

18:46.690 --> 18:48.692
to the most expensive
restaurants in Los Angeles

18:48.736 --> 18:50.390
with the intent
to extort them for money

18:50.433 --> 18:53.175
in the form of wine, food...
- Those men expected to pay.

18:53.219 --> 18:54.481
That's the thing.
No, they didn't.

18:54.524 --> 18:56.178
Margo invited them.
She made the reservation.

18:56.222 --> 18:58.180
She told them to order
whatever they wanted.

18:58.224 --> 19:00.051
Then she had her fill
of food and drink,

19:00.095 --> 19:01.792
made an excuse, left the table,
and never came back.

19:01.836 --> 19:04.491
She is from an era
when men and women--

19:04.534 --> 19:06.754
[ cellphone buzzing ]Are you seriously using
19th century gender norms

19:06.797 --> 19:08.756
as your defense?

19:08.799 --> 19:09.365
[ buzzing continues ]Is that your girlfriend?

19:09.409 --> 19:10.975
What? Yeah.

19:11.019 --> 19:13.021
- You make a cute couple.
- Thanks.

19:13.064 --> 19:14.631
Who picked up the tab
on your first date?

19:14.675 --> 19:18.505
Margo Baxter is a grifter,
and you know that.

19:18.548 --> 19:20.159
Ah, I should check in
with the office.

19:20.202 --> 19:22.509
If you promise
not to bogart my sandwich,

19:22.552 --> 19:25.338
I promise to come back
with a real sentencing offer.

19:25.381 --> 19:27.427
Deal?

19:31.953 --> 19:34.434
[ telephone rings in distance ]

19:34.477 --> 19:36.218
[ indistinct conversations ]

19:36.262 --> 19:38.786
Woman: Okay, babe,
I'll see you inside!

19:38.829 --> 19:41.049
[ telephone rings in distance ]Number 57, ticket, please.

19:41.092 --> 19:42.877
I don't have one.
I'm a judge.

19:42.920 --> 19:44.792
Lola Carmichael,
Department 61.

19:44.835 --> 19:46.054
Did you take a number?

19:46.097 --> 19:47.925
- I did not.
- Then I cannot help you.

19:47.969 --> 19:49.710
I just need to ask you
a couple of questions.

19:49.753 --> 19:51.973
You're not a judge. Judges are
not allowed down here.

19:52.016 --> 19:53.757
Not even a law.
Accepted wisdom.

19:53.801 --> 19:56.282
I left my badge.
It's in my chambers.

19:56.325 --> 19:58.197
Look me up--
Judge Lola Carmichael,

19:58.240 --> 19:59.198
Department 61.[ taps fingers ]

19:59.241 --> 20:03.158
Sherri Kansky is my JA.

20:03.202 --> 20:05.334
You're Sherri's judge.
Right.

20:05.378 --> 20:08.511
Right. Funny.
That's so funny.

20:08.555 --> 20:10.209
What's so--Sorry.
What's so funny?

20:10.252 --> 20:13.037
The way she described you,
I thought you'd be...

20:13.081 --> 20:15.214
What can I do for you,
Your Honor?

20:15.257 --> 20:17.433
I need to ask you
about court costs.

20:17.477 --> 20:18.869
Okay.

20:18.913 --> 20:20.741
[ keyboard clacking ]

20:20.784 --> 20:23.483
[ touchscreen clicking ]

20:25.615 --> 20:26.921
[ whoosh ]

20:26.964 --> 20:28.923
[ telephones ringing
in distance ]

20:28.966 --> 20:30.664
[ cellphone chimes ]

20:34.320 --> 20:37.888
[ sighs ]

20:39.890 --> 20:45.548
[ telephones ringing
indistinct conversations ]

20:49.596 --> 20:51.380
[ indistinct conversations ]

20:51.424 --> 20:55.079
Sister Miranda,
I was hoping we could--

20:55.123 --> 20:58.257
Sorry.
First, I'm sorry if--

20:58.300 --> 21:00.607
if I was a little pushy
when you were on the stand.

21:00.650 --> 21:02.957
You were only doing
your job, Ms. Lopez,

21:03.000 --> 21:04.828
conjuring a defense
for your client.

21:06.395 --> 21:09.050
Were you able to speak
with Mr. Berger, the DDA?

21:09.093 --> 21:11.270
Briefly. I apologized
for any damage

21:11.313 --> 21:13.402
I may have done
to his--his case.

21:13.446 --> 21:15.143
I lost my head a little,

21:15.186 --> 21:17.319
which seems to be happening
these days.

21:17.363 --> 21:19.147
He was very forgiving.

21:19.190 --> 21:20.801
Would you like me
to suggest,

21:20.844 --> 21:22.977
or maybe your church can
help you find, a lawyer?

21:23.020 --> 21:24.805
Am I under arrest?

21:24.848 --> 21:26.850
Sister Miranda,
you need to confess

21:26.894 --> 21:29.810
and return that money
so we can stop this trial.

21:29.853 --> 21:32.029
- Is Phoebe okay?
- She's scared.

21:32.073 --> 21:34.075
And I think she doesn't
want to let you down.

21:34.118 --> 21:37.296
So she didn't send you.

21:37.339 --> 21:40.777
That young woman has
a great faith and a fire.

21:40.821 --> 21:42.910
We're not all
built like that.

21:42.953 --> 21:45.304
Sister Miranda, please.

21:45.347 --> 21:47.567
Will you just come with me
and talk to her?

21:47.610 --> 21:50.221
Phoebe needs your help.

21:50.265 --> 21:52.920
Judge Carmichael needs
to know the truth.

21:52.963 --> 21:55.357
Phoebe, you're innocent.

21:55.401 --> 21:57.664
If Sister Miranda confesses
and returns the money,

21:57.707 --> 21:59.883
there's a chance
no one will be prosecuted.

21:59.927 --> 22:01.058
Phoebe,
maybe we should listen.

22:01.102 --> 22:03.104
No, we're both innocent.

22:03.147 --> 22:05.541
You said all we needed
is reasonable doubt.

22:05.585 --> 22:09.153
Phoebe, why risk this?
You found a home, a life,

22:09.197 --> 22:11.373
and now you're willing
to throw it away.

22:11.417 --> 22:13.767
I have faith.Faith won't get you
acquitted.

22:13.810 --> 22:16.509
No. You will. And our Lord.
I have faith in you both.

22:16.552 --> 22:19.381
I promise you the truth
is your life raft.

22:19.425 --> 22:21.427
Put your faith in the truth.

22:21.470 --> 22:25.169
Miranda, help me.
Trust me.

22:25.213 --> 22:27.520
She isn't guilty of any crime.

22:27.563 --> 22:29.348
That money is for the church,

22:29.391 --> 22:32.307
and the church is the people.

22:32.351 --> 22:34.353
- [ sighs ]
- Right now Sister Miranda is--

22:34.396 --> 22:36.442
She's sick, Ms. Lopez.

22:36.485 --> 22:38.618
I'm not going to let you
or Father Vincent

22:38.661 --> 22:40.141
or anyone else
add to her suffering

22:40.184 --> 22:43.710
or hurt her in any way.

22:43.753 --> 22:45.886
You are my lawyer,
and I'm innocent.

22:45.929 --> 22:48.279
I'm instructing you
to defend me.

22:48.323 --> 22:54.416
♪♪♪

22:54.460 --> 22:56.766
[ mouth full ]
Afternoon, counselor.

22:56.810 --> 22:59.682
[ chuckles ] I officiated
my first marriage

22:59.726 --> 23:01.249
and almost delivered a baby
this morning.

23:01.292 --> 23:03.425
- What you been up to?
- Lola--Uh...

23:03.469 --> 23:05.949
Judge Carmichael, what the hell
are you doing out here?

23:05.993 --> 23:07.603
There's no law that says
that a judge can't go and get

23:07.647 --> 23:10.301
a muffin when she needs one.
- No, there's not. But, uh...

23:10.345 --> 23:12.086
Have you checked out
the court costs lately?

23:12.129 --> 23:13.914
Your Honor, are you sure
this is a good idea?

23:13.957 --> 23:16.438
$28. A penalty of $28
is applied

23:16.482 --> 23:19.398
to every $10 or less
an individual is fined.

23:19.441 --> 23:21.138
Does Sherri know
you're out here?

23:21.182 --> 23:22.792
That's nearly two times
the cost of the fine itself.

23:22.836 --> 23:24.446
I bang my gavel,
and boom,

23:24.490 --> 23:28.929
a $500 fine increases
to $1,400 just like that.

23:28.972 --> 23:30.887
I actually have a preliminary
hearing I need to get to.

23:30.931 --> 23:33.063
- It's not right.
- Can we, uh, can we talk later?

23:33.107 --> 23:34.761
[ elevator bell dings ]Yeah.
I need to get going, too.

23:34.804 --> 23:36.415
All right.

23:37.981 --> 23:40.941
Aw. [ coos ]

23:42.812 --> 23:44.118
Judge Carmichael.

23:44.161 --> 23:45.859
Judge Carmichael,
I need to talk to you.

23:45.902 --> 23:47.643
You sent my husband
to prison.

23:47.687 --> 23:49.428
Now I got my son
up on charges?I apologize.

23:49.471 --> 23:50.951
I don't know what case
you're referring to.

23:50.994 --> 23:52.909
No kidding. You don't care
what happens to us

23:52.953 --> 23:54.911
because you
in all your wisdom

23:54.955 --> 23:56.826
took his only dad
away from him.

23:56.870 --> 23:58.524
You need to stop yelling.How many lives
you ruined today?

23:58.567 --> 24:00.134
- Come with me.
- Get off of me.

24:00.177 --> 24:02.484
Off of me! Get off of me![ handcuffs clicking ]

24:02.528 --> 24:05.400
- Come on.
- Stop it! Let me go!

24:05.444 --> 24:07.402
[ grunts ] Let me go!

24:07.446 --> 24:09.360
This isn't right.
This isn't right!

24:15.671 --> 24:21.677
[ water draining ]

24:21.721 --> 24:23.679
[ sighs ]

24:23.723 --> 24:25.551
Your Honor,
what are you...

24:25.594 --> 24:27.901
[ exhales deeply ]

24:27.944 --> 24:30.991
I needed to stretch my legs.

24:31.034 --> 24:33.820
Not so sure
that was such a good idea.

24:33.863 --> 24:35.778
So now I'm taking
a breather.

24:35.822 --> 24:38.477
- What's up?
- Long story.

24:38.520 --> 24:39.913
[ paper towel rustles ]

24:39.956 --> 24:41.001
Thanks.

24:42.611 --> 24:45.092
Did you get married
in a church, Your Honor?

24:45.135 --> 24:46.485
We did.

24:46.528 --> 24:51.141
So did we.
Made our vows before God.

24:51.185 --> 24:52.534
I know no one cares

24:52.578 --> 24:53.970
about divorce
or anything anymore.

24:54.014 --> 24:57.539
I know it's--
I know the statistics, but I...

24:59.280 --> 25:02.544
I don't...like
breaking my promises.

25:02.588 --> 25:05.895
You didn't break anything,
Emily. He did.

25:05.939 --> 25:07.984
Oh, no. Not to Joe.

25:08.028 --> 25:10.596
You don't have to worry.
I get that. I just...

25:10.639 --> 25:12.467
I-I mean...

25:12.511 --> 25:14.295
[ inhales and exhales deeply ]

25:14.338 --> 25:15.557
To God?

25:15.601 --> 25:19.126
My family? My friends?

25:19.169 --> 25:20.519
I stood up there, and I...

25:22.695 --> 25:24.305
This sounds really weird,
doesn't it?

25:24.348 --> 25:26.133
I think I've just been
hanging out with nuns too much.

25:26.176 --> 25:27.438
[ chuckles ]

25:27.482 --> 25:28.396
Your Honor.

25:39.363 --> 25:43.672
Anyone who knows you
knows you do the right thing.

25:49.896 --> 25:51.985
See you back in court,
Ms. Lopez.

25:54.030 --> 25:55.510
[ door closes ]

25:55.554 --> 25:58.818
Respect for the institution,
Your Honor.

25:58.861 --> 26:01.864
[ sniffs ] Ooh.These aren't empty traditions.
They have a purpose,

26:01.908 --> 26:04.650
and youhave been in this
courthouse long enough...

26:04.693 --> 26:06.695
Sherri, can I interrupt
this lecture

26:06.739 --> 26:10.046
to ask you a question?
- As long as we keep moving.

26:10.090 --> 26:11.787
What's the formula for
converting an unpaid fine

26:11.831 --> 26:15.095
into jail time?
- $150 equals 1 day, Your Honor.

26:15.138 --> 26:16.966
So for every $150
in unpaid fines,

26:17.010 --> 26:18.968
I can convert that
to a defendant

26:19.012 --> 26:20.709
spending one day in county jail?
- Correct,

26:20.753 --> 26:23.625
as long as the fine equals
no less than 15 days in jail.

26:23.669 --> 26:25.584
Meaning I can't throw someone
in the slammer

26:25.627 --> 26:28.325
for a parking ticket.
- Eye on the ball, Your Honor.

26:28.369 --> 26:29.805
There is still a rogue nun
to deal with.

26:29.849 --> 26:32.199
I need you to contact
Mr. Owens from this morning.

26:32.242 --> 26:34.505
Tell him I need
to see him back in court.Certainly.

26:34.549 --> 26:37.247
[ door creaks open ]

26:37.291 --> 26:39.946
[ exhales deeply ]

26:39.989 --> 26:42.905
[ indistinct conversations ]

26:44.646 --> 26:46.735
Callan, still salty about lunch?

26:46.779 --> 26:48.955
You gonna charge me
with felony pranking?

26:48.998 --> 26:50.347
- Ha.
- Remind me, how many

26:50.391 --> 26:52.436
of your victims
in the hallway bailed?

26:52.480 --> 26:54.917
A few.Ah. Good thing you didn't
take that bet.

26:54.961 --> 26:56.658
She has expensive tastes.

26:56.702 --> 26:58.529
You should put your client
on the stand.

26:58.573 --> 27:00.619
I'd love to talk to her
when she's under oath.

27:00.662 --> 27:02.577
It's a preliminary hearing,
remember?

27:02.621 --> 27:04.535
That's the part where
you show meall your cards.

27:04.579 --> 27:06.973
And she holds hers
close to her chest.

27:09.105 --> 27:11.934
All rise. Department 61
of the Los Angeles Supreme--

27:11.978 --> 27:14.415
That's all right. I think
they know. Sorry for the delay.

27:14.458 --> 27:16.939
I needed to pop over
to Judge Benner's courtroom

27:16.983 --> 27:18.288
and clear out
a few happy couples.

27:18.332 --> 27:20.726
Mr. Callan, what else you got?

27:20.769 --> 27:22.815
Your Honor, the People call
Detective Curtis Perry

27:22.858 --> 27:25.818
to the stand, the lead
investigator in the case.

27:25.861 --> 27:28.081
Ms. Lopez, you may
resume your cross.

27:32.476 --> 27:38.004
♪♪♪

27:38.047 --> 27:41.050
Ms. Lopez.
Any more questions?

27:46.839 --> 27:48.536
[ chair wheels roll ]

27:48.579 --> 27:49.755
No further questions,
Your Honor.

27:49.798 --> 27:51.452
[ chair creaks ]

27:51.495 --> 27:53.062
Mr. Berger?

27:53.106 --> 27:54.716
Um...

27:54.760 --> 27:57.458
No redirect.
No additional witnesses.

27:57.501 --> 27:59.199
People rest, Your Honor.

28:00.461 --> 28:03.769
[ gallery murmuring ]

28:03.812 --> 28:05.466
Witness may step down.

28:07.033 --> 28:08.382
Thank you.

28:09.992 --> 28:11.428
What's the plan now?

28:14.823 --> 28:17.565
Ms. Lopez, any witnesses?

28:17.608 --> 28:20.786
[ bar door swings open ]

28:20.829 --> 28:22.657
The defense calls
Sister Phoebe McKenzie

28:22.701 --> 28:24.659
to the stand, Your Honor.
- [ whispers ] What?

28:24.703 --> 28:26.966
[ lowered voice ] God helps
those who help themselves.

28:27.009 --> 28:28.881
You're gonna go up there,
and we're gonna convince

28:28.924 --> 28:29.882
the judge
that you're innocent

28:29.925 --> 28:31.797
because you are.
That's the plan.

28:40.719 --> 28:42.416
Mark: Felony extortion.

28:42.459 --> 28:44.679
Define extortion for us,
detective.

28:44.723 --> 28:46.333
Obtaining property
by inducing--

28:46.376 --> 28:47.769
Obtaining property
by inducing consent

28:47.813 --> 28:49.684
via wrongful use
of force or fear.

28:49.728 --> 28:51.773
I know the law, gentlemen.
This is not a jury trial.

28:51.817 --> 28:53.470
I'd just like to know

28:53.514 --> 28:55.385
how extortion is applied
in this case.

28:55.429 --> 28:57.126
Seems quite novel.

28:57.170 --> 28:59.607
Apply it in this case,
then.

28:59.650 --> 29:01.435
The property,
food and liquor, obtained

29:01.478 --> 29:02.741
by forcing the victim--

29:02.784 --> 29:04.177
Objection.
There's no evidence

29:04.220 --> 29:06.396
my client forced anyone
to do anything.

29:06.440 --> 29:08.181
Who did Margo Baxter think
would pay for dinner?

29:08.224 --> 29:10.531
Objection! I have no idea
what she was thinking,

29:10.574 --> 29:13.186
and neither do you.Sustained.
Try again, Mr. Callan.

29:13.229 --> 29:16.406
Detective,
who did the victims tell you

29:16.450 --> 29:19.018
they thought was going to pay?
- The defendant.

29:19.061 --> 29:20.628
She asked them out.
She chose the place.

29:20.671 --> 29:22.586
She made the reservation.

29:22.630 --> 29:25.328
She did the ordering
each and every time.

29:25.372 --> 29:27.417
And what did they tell you
they were afraid of?

29:27.461 --> 29:29.680
Leaving a restaurant
without paying is a crime.

29:29.724 --> 29:31.291
Victims were afraid
they'd be charged

29:31.334 --> 29:32.727
if they didn't pay the bill
in full.

29:32.771 --> 29:34.468
They also feared being
barred from returning.

29:34.511 --> 29:36.687
Oh, boo-hoo. It's L.A.
Find another restaurant.

29:36.731 --> 29:38.472
Ms. Quinn,
will your client pipe down,

29:38.515 --> 29:41.301
or are we moving
into contempt territory?

29:41.344 --> 29:44.130
Thank you.
No more questions.

29:44.173 --> 29:45.827
[ indistinct murmuring ]

29:45.871 --> 29:49.700
- Ms. Quinn, care to cross?
- Yes, please.

29:49.744 --> 29:52.616
Detective Perry,
did anyone order you

29:52.660 --> 29:54.314
to investigate
these little tips

29:54.357 --> 29:56.011
that are technically
hearsay?

29:56.055 --> 29:57.534
- No.
- So I'm sorry.

29:57.578 --> 29:59.798
- Why did you do it?
- Because she broke the law.

29:59.841 --> 30:01.800
Right. So-called extortion.

30:01.843 --> 30:04.367
You decided that she was
an evil extortionist.

30:04.411 --> 30:06.543
Objection. Argumentative.Sustained.
Final warning, counselor.

30:06.587 --> 30:08.850
Yes, Your Honor.

30:08.894 --> 30:11.505
Did you tell any of
your colleagues it was because

30:11.548 --> 30:13.899
the alleged perpetrator
was a woman?

30:13.942 --> 30:17.206
I said if a man was doing this,
people would be all over it,

30:17.250 --> 30:18.555
but because it's a woman

30:18.599 --> 30:20.601
rolling over some lonely guys,
it's okay?

30:20.644 --> 30:23.647
So you pursued these
small alleged infractions

30:23.691 --> 30:25.345
because Margo was a woman?

30:25.388 --> 30:28.478
In fact, you targeted my client
becauseshe is a woman.

30:28.522 --> 30:29.697
- Objection.
- Sustained.

30:29.740 --> 30:31.133
When was the last time
you had a date...

30:31.177 --> 30:32.613
Sustained!...since your divorce,
Detective?

30:32.656 --> 30:34.789
Excuse me?

30:34.833 --> 30:36.486
I think I'm done.

30:40.447 --> 30:45.408
Unless you have anything
further, Mr. Callan?

30:46.366 --> 30:49.543
I think we know how this
particular dance will end.

30:49.586 --> 30:53.025
♪♪♪

30:53.068 --> 30:54.896
My mom said
that if there was a God,

30:54.940 --> 30:56.550
we'd have cheap rent.

30:56.593 --> 30:59.814
She moved us in
with her boyfriends, mostly.

30:59.858 --> 31:03.209
I left when I was 14.
It was bad on the street.

31:03.252 --> 31:04.601
I was bad.

31:04.645 --> 31:06.473
Got into drugs
for a few years.

31:06.516 --> 31:09.432
Took people's...money,

31:09.476 --> 31:10.825
checks, credit cards.

31:10.869 --> 31:13.175
- You got caught?
- Yeah.

31:13.219 --> 31:16.004
Jail was...

31:16.048 --> 31:19.486
it was bad.
Worse than people think.

31:20.966 --> 31:22.619
How did you end up
with the Church?

31:22.663 --> 31:26.145
I got out,
ended up on the Skid.

31:26.188 --> 31:27.494
Sister Miranda was there

31:27.537 --> 31:30.453
handing out bottled water
and sandwiches.

31:30.497 --> 31:32.542
But she listened, too.

31:32.586 --> 31:34.327
She knew that's what
some of us really needed.

31:34.370 --> 31:38.505
She was so--so calm.

31:38.548 --> 31:40.420
I wanted that, too,

31:40.463 --> 31:43.814
so one day
I followed her there.

31:43.858 --> 31:45.120
I wouldn't leave.

31:45.164 --> 31:48.819
Could you pick one word
to describe the Church?

31:48.863 --> 31:51.039
What is it to you?

31:52.519 --> 31:53.650
Love.

31:55.565 --> 31:57.089
It never goes away.

31:58.873 --> 32:00.527
Phoebe, for the record,

32:00.570 --> 32:03.225
did you take that money
from your church?

32:03.269 --> 32:04.444
[ whispering indistinctly ]

32:04.487 --> 32:06.707
I'm sorry. Can you
repeat the question?

32:06.750 --> 32:08.535
Did you take that money
from your church?

32:08.578 --> 32:16.369
♪♪♪

32:18.023 --> 32:20.329
Phoebe?

32:20.373 --> 32:22.636
- Your Honor.
- I'm guilty!

32:22.679 --> 32:24.290
I need to confer
with my client.

32:24.333 --> 32:25.117
I'm sorry.
I have to tell the truth.

32:25.160 --> 32:27.467
I'm--I'm guilty.

32:27.510 --> 32:31.297
♪♪♪

32:38.304 --> 32:41.133
[ indistinct conversations ]

32:46.051 --> 32:48.270
I'll tell you
what I just told her.

32:48.314 --> 32:50.316
If this continues,
I will withdraw as her lawyer.

32:50.359 --> 32:52.318
I can't and won't
knowingly ask questions

32:52.361 --> 32:54.363
that will lead
to false answers.

32:54.407 --> 32:57.366
If Sister Phoebe sticks
to this confession,

32:57.410 --> 33:01.718
she is committing perjury
for you.

33:01.762 --> 33:03.894
Are you going
to let her do that?

33:06.375 --> 33:08.769
Congratulations.
You fight dirty.

33:08.812 --> 33:11.076
Also a massive step back
for gender politics.

33:11.119 --> 33:12.903
The cops tried to
bootstrap it into a felony.

33:12.947 --> 33:16.342
Didn't fly.12 victims.
$10,000 of stolen meals.

33:16.385 --> 33:18.083
Maybe seeing the inside
of a jail cell

33:18.126 --> 33:19.345
would have stopped her.

33:19.388 --> 33:20.999
Charges dismissed.
Thank you.

33:21.042 --> 33:23.566
It's not smart
to antagonize a DDA.

33:23.610 --> 33:24.741
Well, it's what
you've been doing.

33:24.785 --> 33:26.961
I've been doing my job.
Prelim's over.

33:27.005 --> 33:28.354
And for the record,

33:28.397 --> 33:29.877
you treated those men
like garbage.

33:29.920 --> 33:32.184
- She has a soul.
- After business hours.

33:32.227 --> 33:35.361
Enjoy your life, Margo,
at Craft or Patina

33:35.404 --> 33:37.363
or wherever
you break a heart next.

33:37.406 --> 33:38.842
- Ah, that's gonna be difficult.
- Why is that?

33:38.886 --> 33:40.061
I've spoken
with all the restaurants

33:40.105 --> 33:41.454
involved in the case.

33:41.497 --> 33:43.717
They've been spreading
the word and your photo.

33:43.760 --> 33:45.675
You're gonna be banned from
all the prime spots in town.

33:45.719 --> 33:47.503
Oh, no.
That can't be legal.

33:47.547 --> 33:50.115
Mm. It is, but feel free
to discuss it

33:50.158 --> 33:52.943
with a different lawyer.
- But...what will I do

33:52.987 --> 33:54.467
with all those
Saturday nights?

33:54.510 --> 33:56.730
You should have thought
about that before.

33:59.820 --> 34:01.213
That was cold.

34:01.256 --> 34:04.564
Too bad we didn't make
that bet. I'm hungry.

34:04.607 --> 34:07.306
- I have plans anyway.
- Right.

34:08.916 --> 34:10.135
She's pretty.

34:13.703 --> 34:16.010
When you're ready
to take meto dinner, call me.

34:16.054 --> 34:18.056
I'll pick up the check.

34:18.099 --> 34:24.062
♪♪♪

34:24.105 --> 34:26.673
Mr. Owens, the court
has reviewed your sentence

34:26.716 --> 34:29.719
and has increased your fine
to $2,000.

34:29.763 --> 34:31.286
It was $500 before.

34:31.330 --> 34:32.505
You know,
with this kind of help,

34:32.548 --> 34:35.029
I might as well check
into Men's Central.

34:35.073 --> 34:36.204
Your Honor...

34:36.248 --> 34:37.771
Given the degree
of financial hardship,

34:37.814 --> 34:41.122
the court is prepared to convert
that fine to jail time.

34:41.166 --> 34:43.255
So you're sending me
to jail?

34:43.298 --> 34:45.039
That conversion comes out
to 16 days.

34:45.083 --> 34:47.128
Now, that sentence will
most certainly be reduced

34:47.172 --> 34:48.521
by the sheriff
due to overcrowding.

34:48.564 --> 34:50.131
That and the fact
that an individual usually

34:50.175 --> 34:53.265
only serves 10%
of the conversion time

34:53.308 --> 34:55.180
means you should be
booked and released

34:55.223 --> 34:56.659
within a few hours.

34:56.703 --> 34:59.227
Your Honor, with respect,
I don't understand.

34:59.271 --> 35:01.142
You will be on probation,
Mr. Owens,

35:01.186 --> 35:03.927
but you will be free to go,
and you won't owe us a penny.

35:03.971 --> 35:06.582
That sound fair?

35:06.626 --> 35:07.670
Yes.

35:09.194 --> 35:11.326
Thank you.

35:11.370 --> 35:14.199
- Thank you, Your Honor.
- This is your last chance.

35:14.242 --> 35:16.592
Now, I don't want
to see you in here again

35:16.636 --> 35:18.116
and especially
without a lawyer.

35:21.336 --> 35:22.772
[ whispers ] Thank you.

35:26.472 --> 35:27.516
Attorney: Your Honor.

35:34.132 --> 35:35.481
[ door closes ]

35:37.526 --> 35:39.963
[ creaks]

35:43.228 --> 35:45.012
You--

35:45.055 --> 35:48.276
You've been driving around
with $100,000 in your trunk?

35:48.320 --> 35:50.887
No one's gonna break
into this car.

35:50.931 --> 35:52.541
This money was meant
to do better--

35:52.585 --> 35:55.240
food, medicine,
housing for the poor.

35:55.283 --> 35:56.806
Not the rectory.

35:59.983 --> 36:01.898
Phoebe was the first
to figure it out.

36:01.942 --> 36:03.204
She refused to...

36:04.814 --> 36:06.207
She protected me.

36:06.251 --> 36:09.384
You still have--
It's all here?

36:09.428 --> 36:13.171
Yes. After I took it,
I felt lost.

36:13.214 --> 36:14.998
Well, why--
why did you let Phoebe--

36:15.042 --> 36:16.913
Because she is innocent.

36:16.957 --> 36:18.828
We both had faith

36:18.872 --> 36:21.701
the justice system
would see that.

36:21.744 --> 36:23.877
I shouldn't have let her.

36:23.920 --> 36:27.272
I got scared of everything,

36:27.315 --> 36:29.578
of dying, of...

36:29.622 --> 36:33.408
dying without the embrace
of my church.

36:33.452 --> 36:34.931
I don't want to leave.

36:42.548 --> 36:44.114
How's it going, Carmichael?

36:45.420 --> 36:47.030
Feeling limber?

36:47.074 --> 36:48.728
Legs stretched enough?

36:48.771 --> 36:50.469
Every day is an adventure.

36:50.512 --> 36:51.687
Mm.

36:51.731 --> 36:53.646
What happened to you today?

36:53.689 --> 36:54.864
Traffic.

36:54.908 --> 36:57.127
For nine hours?

36:57.171 --> 36:58.128
[ scoffs ]

37:02.089 --> 37:04.265
I've always liked
Wedding Day.

37:04.309 --> 37:07.921
When you marry
two people in love, it's...

37:07.964 --> 37:09.792
[ sighs ] You don't have
to be impartial.

37:09.836 --> 37:11.751
My whole life,
I've liked weddings.

37:11.794 --> 37:15.233
But I've always felt
on the outside.

37:15.276 --> 37:17.060
I was married once.

37:17.104 --> 37:22.109
Mm. But even then,
they weren't for me.

37:22.152 --> 37:25.765
Since 2013,
I have had the honor

37:25.808 --> 37:29.856
of marrying same-sex couples,
and it's an absolute joy.

37:29.899 --> 37:31.814
[ chuckles ]

37:31.858 --> 37:34.382
Unless it's on the same day
that your girlfriend,

37:34.426 --> 37:37.994
your partner
of four years...

37:38.038 --> 37:40.040
dumps you.

37:40.083 --> 37:41.781
[ scoffs ]

37:41.824 --> 37:46.307
I... [ scoffs ]

37:46.351 --> 37:49.049
I know when it's a good idea
to take a mental health day,

37:49.092 --> 37:50.746
and it was...

37:52.357 --> 37:54.837
it was a first.

37:54.881 --> 37:56.274
I'm so sorry.

37:59.929 --> 38:02.367
I wasn't gonna implement
Wedding Day

38:02.410 --> 38:04.934
at this courthouse until...

38:04.978 --> 38:08.068
everybodycould take part.

38:08.111 --> 38:11.332
It's the most important thing
I've done in my career.

38:11.376 --> 38:14.944
I have got
some catching up to do.

38:18.208 --> 38:19.775
Hang in there, Carmichael.

38:19.819 --> 38:22.343
This is a privilege,

38:22.387 --> 38:24.519
and you get way more
than you give up.

38:30.395 --> 38:31.744
[ knock on door ]

38:33.572 --> 38:36.314
Your Honor, there is something
you need to know about.

38:43.843 --> 38:46.236
I am satisfied
that the People have proven

38:46.280 --> 38:48.108
that the defendant
committed the crime

38:48.151 --> 38:49.501
beyond a reasonable doubt,

38:49.544 --> 38:52.373
and I find her
guilty on the charge.

38:52.417 --> 38:54.419
But I don't think

38:54.462 --> 38:56.812
a felony conviction
is appropriate.

38:56.856 --> 38:58.640
The money has returned,

38:58.684 --> 39:01.077
and the defendant was honest
about her past

39:01.121 --> 39:02.775
and her commitment
to move forward.

39:02.818 --> 39:05.821
So I will exercise
my discretion

39:05.865 --> 39:08.215
under Penal Code Section 17B

39:08.258 --> 39:11.218
and reduce the charge
to a misdemeanor.

39:11.261 --> 39:13.438
The defendant is placed
on summary probation

39:13.481 --> 39:17.267
for 12 months under
the following conditions--

39:17.311 --> 39:21.228
100 hours of community service
with Father Vincent.

39:21.271 --> 39:23.361
So does the defendant accept?

39:24.797 --> 39:26.320
I do.

39:26.364 --> 39:27.277
Then this court is adjourned.

39:27.321 --> 39:29.410
[ gavel bangs ]

39:29.454 --> 39:30.193
[ gallery murmuring ]

39:30.237 --> 39:34.546
Oh!

39:34.589 --> 39:35.721
Thank you.

39:35.764 --> 39:38.288
[ indistinct conversations ]

39:38.332 --> 39:42.249
You, uh,
you keep your promises

39:42.292 --> 39:43.816
by having faith
in yourself.

39:45.470 --> 39:47.341
God loves you.

39:47.385 --> 39:58.526
♪♪♪

39:58.570 --> 40:02.269
Now let's get some people
married!

40:02.312 --> 40:04.880
[ cheers and applause ]♪ I can see the daylight♪

40:04.924 --> 40:08.623
♪ I can see the daylight
from the dawn♪

40:08.667 --> 40:11.670
♪ I can see the sunrise♪

40:11.713 --> 40:14.150
♪ I can see the sunrise
won't be long♪

40:14.194 --> 40:17.763
I'm sorry about today.

40:17.806 --> 40:20.635
I needed to stretch my legs

40:20.679 --> 40:23.159
and almost had them
both broken.

40:23.203 --> 40:26.946
I suggest in the future
a yoga mat in chambers.

40:26.989 --> 40:29.470
♪♪♪

40:29.514 --> 40:31.254
That was nimble.

40:31.298 --> 40:33.300
Nimble work there today
with Mr. Owens.

40:33.343 --> 40:36.042
The justice system needs
to stop funding itself

40:36.085 --> 40:39.045
on the backs of defendants.

40:39.088 --> 40:41.613
Is this the dream,
the mass wedding?

40:41.656 --> 40:42.875
Yes.

40:42.918 --> 40:44.485
[ laughter ]

40:44.529 --> 40:46.661
Yes, it is.

40:46.705 --> 40:48.576
[ projecting voice ]
This will be orderly.

40:48.620 --> 40:51.710
This will be simple.
This will be very romantic.

40:51.753 --> 40:53.712
The building closes
in an hour, wedding folks.

40:53.755 --> 40:55.496
Let's get...this...done.[ claps hands ]

40:55.540 --> 40:57.716
I need everyone
to line up in your pairs.

40:57.759 --> 40:59.326
Orderly, thank you.
Let's get...this...going.

40:59.369 --> 41:01.415
You were hard
to keep up with today.

41:01.459 --> 41:03.330
I had a nun to defend.

41:03.373 --> 41:05.158
Recovering Catholic.
The guilt is brutal.

41:05.201 --> 41:06.464
Hmm.

